caption.body: The Aviation Museum and Library is closed today to observe Indigenous People’s Day and will reopen tomorrow, October 15th at 10am. All other exhibitions located in the airport terminals are still available to view: https://ow.ly/g2Ym50TKOvQ  SFO Museum respectfully acknowledges that we are on the unceded ancestral homeland of the Ramaytush Ohlone—the original, present, and future inhabitants and stewards of the San Francisco Peninsula. Please join us in recognizing and honoring Ramaytush Ohlone ancestors, descendants, and all Indigenous communities who have inhabited and will continue to inhabit the Bay Area for hundreds of generations.
